<body background="@website_root@/images/bg.jpg" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#993300" vlink="#993300">
<table width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td width="80"></td>
		<td>
			<dd align="left"><img src="@website_root@/images/balsa.jpg" alt="balsa" align="middle" width="476" height="122"><big><big><b>Features</b></big></big><br></dd>
			<p>Balsa is an e-mail client. It is part of the GNOME desktop environment. Balsa's interface
			is similar to that of Eudora on Windows, with many of its features.
			</p>
			<p><font face="lucida, helvetica, arial">It supports:</font>
			<ul>
				<li>Local mailboxes (mbox, maildir, mh)</li>
				<li>Nested mailboxes (see <a href="@website_root@/screens/mainwindow.jpg">this</a>)</li>
				<li>POP3</li>
				<li>IMAP</li>
				<li>Printing</li>
				<li>Spell Checking</li>
				<li>Multi-threaded mail retrevial (optional)</li>
				<li>MIME support (view images inline, save parts)</li>
				<li>Supports both SMTP and the use of a local MTA</li>
				<li>Address Book that integrates with GnomeCard</li>
				<li>Great configurability</li>
				<li>Active, open development (Mailing list info at <a href="http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo/balsa-list/">http://mail.gnome.org/mailman/listinfo/balsa-list/</a>)</li>
				<li>Multiple character sets for composing and reading messages</li>
				<li>Attach files</li>
			</ul>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
</body>


